        void WriteEndStartTag(bool empty) {
            ...
            xmlEncoder.EndAttribute();
            if (empty) {
                textWriter.Write(&quot; /&quot;); // space-slash
            }
            textWriter.Write(&#39;&gt;&#39;);
        }

If you _really_ need to get rid of that space, roll your own XML serializer, or edit the file as text instead of XML. The latter alternative ignores XML validation, so be extra careful not to wreck the config file.

